            <div type="note">
                <head>Tour of 1828</head>
                <p>The Ruskins planned a &#x201C;great tour&#x201D; of the Lakes in 1828, intended to compensate
                    for the leaner years of 1826 and 1827. First to plan the tour, and then to
                    record its progress, Ruskin initially devoted MS IVB to Travel Itinerary and
                    Tour Notes, 1828, which consists of itineraries and notes for this trip.
                    Ultimately, the plans were not fulfilled until 1830, the 1828 journey having
                    been interrupted on 24 May by news of the 12 May death of &#x201C;Aunt Jessie,&#x201D; John
                    James&#x02BC;s sister, Mrs. Patrick Richardson (see <hi rend="italic">Tour to the
                        Lakes</hi>, 7; and Ruskin, <hi rend="italic">Works</hi>, 35:70, where the
                    death is mistakenly ascribed to 1829).</p>
            </div>
